<sn><md>### Course Learning Outcomes (CLOs)

Upon completion, students will be able to:

* **CLO 1:** Describe key concepts of ecology, ecological processes, and the links between species, habitats, and ecosystem dynamics.
* **CLO 2:** Identify key relationships between soil biota and the ecosystem, and understand how biodiversity and soil processes relate to one another.
* **CLO 3:** Explain major biodiversity conservation techniques and the principles of population dynamics.
* **CLO 4:** Identify problems within eco-tourism and develop strategies to resolve them.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                        | Details                                                                                                                                  |
| ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Ecology**                  | Definitions<br>scope<br>principles of thermodynamics in relation to ecology<br>freshwater, marine, estuarine, and radiation ecology      |
| **Ecosystem**                | Definition<br>structure<br>components<br>primary and secondary production<br>energy flow<br>food chains and food webs<br>energy exchange |
| **Community Dynamics**       | Ecological succession<br>types of succession<br>succession process<br>stabilization                                                      |
| **Ecological Interactions**  | Plant/microbe, animal/microbe, animal/animal relationships<br>mutualism<br>competition<br>commensalism<br>parasitism<br>predation        |
| **Biomass and Biodiversity** | Microbial biomass<br>levels and types of biodiversity<br>global biodiversity crisis and loss<br>conservation techniques                  |
| **Soil Biotechnology**       | Genetically modified plants and microbes                                                                                                 |
| **Population Growth**        | Growth theories<br>fertility<br>mortality<br>migration<br>population change factors<br>world and Bangladesh growth patterns              |
| **Ecotourism**               | Definition<br>natural and manmade tourist spots in Bangladesh<br>prospects and drawbacks<br>popularization strategies                    |
| **Values of Ecotourism**     | Aesthetic, scientific, and educational values<br>parks and protected areas (IUCN categories)<br>institutional frameworks in Bangladesh   |
</md></sn><sn><md>### Recommended Readings

* Ecology
* Essentials of Ecology
* Soil Ecology
* Ecology: Concepts and Applications
* A Handbook on Analysis of Soil, Plant and Water
